Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Glean*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, RAG and AI agents, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the React.js and TypeScript depth this position demands. At Sperse, I built developer-facing code solutions using TypeScript and React — API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows — that required the same cross-functional collaboration with product designers and backend engineers that Glean values in this role. I also architected an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints, requiring rigorous API contract design and input validation. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith — covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks — reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and routing optimizations. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I contributed directly to building user interfaces with React.js, TypeScript, Spring Boot, and AWS that supported thousands of users across 30+ applications — giving me hands-on experience owning features end-to-end from inception to launch and beyond. I also designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO. Together, these roles have prepared me to build delightful user interfaces and contribute meaningfully to Glean's frontend engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that align directly with the engineering discipline and customer-focused collaborative culture Glean values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster. I led workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students — breaking down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly. This mirrors the mentoring aspect of this role and reflects my proactive attitude toward knowledge-sharing and cross-functional collaboration.

I have always been passionate about expanding human potential to do extraordinary work through AI, and making AI accessible to every employee across an organization. I am excited to contribute to Glean's mission of turning the superintelligent enterprise from concept into reality by shipping polished, zero-latency user interfaces that integrate the Glean experience into every workflow. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

